sp.p:
This is plain-dealing, and without hypocrisie;
Could the City of London swallow
this?

But the Articles of this Petition were not
all the same with those of his former Instrument;
for now there was to be another House;
and whereas before his Council was to name his
Successors, he had Power now to do it himself;
so that he was an absolute Monarch, and might
leave the Succession to his Son, if he would;
and so successively, or transfer it to whom he
pleas'd. The Ceremony being ended, the Parliament
adjourn'd to the 20th of January following,
and then the other House also sate with
their Fellows.
